transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra. This is Charles.

Speaker 2: Yes, sir. This is David Harrison.

Speaker 1: How are we doing, David?

Speaker 2: Well, I'm doing pretty good. I had canceled a subscription back in December,

Speaker 1: and all of a sudden I got a charge on my bank account for $163.95,

Speaker 2: and I did not request any more bills.

Speaker 1: Okay. David Harrison, Lukedale, Mississippi.

Speaker 2: Yeah, Lukedale, Mississippi.

Speaker 1: All right. How did you try to cancel it back in December?

Speaker 2: Did you call?

Speaker 1: I called you, fellas.

Speaker 2: Oh. Did you maybe call the pharmacy by mistake because we'll all bill?

Speaker 1: No, no. I actually called you guys.

Speaker 2: Yikes. Okay. I'm not calling you a liar or anything, David,

Speaker 1: Well, I mean, like I said, I did not get a chip in January so that it would just stop.

Speaker 2: Right. So that's why I'm worried that you called the pharmacy

Speaker 1: because all they're going to do is delay the next order.

Speaker 2: So, look, here's what I can do. I can cancel everything going forward.

Speaker 1: This order is on its way. If you don't want it, it's going to arrive by Tuesday.

Speaker 2: All you need to do is write return to sender on it with a marker or a pen,

Speaker 1: throw it back in the mailbox.

Speaker 2: Mailman will take it and send it right back to us for a refund, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay. Sounds good to me.

Speaker 2: Okay. Just out of curiosity, David, how were you doing on the pills, though?

Speaker 1: Well, I don't know. They didn't seem to be working that last set.

Speaker 2: You know, usually you see blue lights or whatever, and they weren't working.

Speaker 1: So I don't know if they were a bad batch or just generic, whatever it was.

Speaker 2: Okay. If you're interested, I can see if my pharmacy can send over a version of the AGV

Speaker 1: that's made in our France factory for free.

Speaker 2: I can send you ten free pills if you're willing to try them

Speaker 1: and see if these ones are giving you the activation that you're looking for,

Speaker 2: the kick that you're looking for.

Speaker 1: And if they do, call us back and let us know,

Speaker 2: and we can start accommodating with this pill that I send

Speaker 1: rather than the old one that you've been getting.

Speaker 2: Okay. Yeah, I like the old one. They weren't really doing it for me, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay. All right. Yeah, maybe we just need to pivot a little bit.

Speaker 2: So I'll send the request into the pharmacy today.

Speaker 1: I'd expect the pills to arrive by maybe Thursday or Friday of next week,

Speaker 2: depending on weather and whatnot.

Speaker 1: Well, there's no rush. I'm on the road.

Speaker 2: I don't want to get home by, you know, once a month.

Speaker 1: Gotcha.

Speaker 2: There's no rush on that.

Speaker 1: Okay. The pills that you're going to be looking for that I send

Speaker 2: will have the number 100 pressed onto them like a stamp.

Speaker 1: That's how you're able to tell the difference, so just keep that in mind, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay, Bob. I appreciate your help, sir.

Speaker 1: Absolutely. All right, David. I hope you have a great rest of your day.

Speaker 2: You too, Glenn. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Take care.
